A jet of flames burst from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki incinerated a precise patch of the forest, then flew in circles above, observing it for a time. Oddly, as he slowed, the weird cries of shouts behind him had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Hey Tenuk, you've already changed into Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I'm not lifted violently by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's not that unpleasant, is it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi, he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws in Thassalin's back, so much so that he had made the Thraki bleed, but clearly he didn't care. However, Thassalin had realized that he had terrorized his new friends and had found a clearing to land.
"SORRY, I SMELLED SOMETHING. I SHOULD HAVE CHECKED."
"You had to drag us here with you?", Tenuk shouted as he slid down the back of Thassalin. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our great and strong warrior! How is he going to catch up to us?"
"He'll find a way," Nissy retorted. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"All right, but can Retvik drive?"
Nissy blinked her eyes and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He has nothing like your truck, and I've never seen him drive something as cute as Kayel's little car, and if he started coming to work in a car, it's only because YOU drive us there. He just has a bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly overcome with laughter and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him a bit too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I PICTURED YOUR TALL FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A LITTLE BIKE MEANT FOR KIDDOS, SUCH A COMEDY! I WOULD HAVE LOVED TO HAVE TELEPATHY. THAT'S A PRECIOUS THOUGHT THAT I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin must have thought. "Yes, that's just it. But what did you gather and why did you fly off so quickly?"
Thassalin let out a roar, lifted off, and briefly disappeared, before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a golden and white draconic creature, very rare. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI COMMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE CLOSE."
The powerful Thraki froze suddenly. Nyssi and Kayel too, their attention drawn by a gap in the clearing. Whatever it was, this thing opened two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, without worrying about the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to get out of the way just in time, but Nyssi found herself dragged and almost thrown at Thassalin.
Thassalin reacts to the aggression by grabbing Nissy and throwing her over his back, with the aid of his extraordinary length and dexterity tail, before taking off. The two-winged black creature rushed quickly in pursuit.
Kayel blew out while drawing the rifle he had on his back, then opened a pouch in which a bandolier was located. He put it over his shoulder so that he could easily access it, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thracian, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to transform into something that can fly?", Kayel asked.
"Want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And then? I have an ultra-powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to serve. I only need to see him to shoot at him."
Tenuk hesitated, then backed off to give himself a bit of space. In a weak, slightly pained growl, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales and his arms turned into wings. He quickly became the normal pale blue Thraki again, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb."
Having regained a more normal Thracian appearance, Tenuk now had scaly plates covering his back, but a pair of horns had also grown there, useful for Kayel to hold onto. Tenuk needed a little time to take off, but once airborne, he quickly oriented himself and attempted to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature burst forth from below, and Tenuk managed to avoid it just in time.
I suppose it's the other big scary monster that was bothering Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow trying to pull the second beastie, missed his target and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tunik does not react. He was too focused on his flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature pursuing them. Kayel clumsily spun around himself to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them proved to be a blessing for Kayel, as it allowed him to aim and shoot more easily. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, which let out a cry of pain before disappearing again under the trees. Kayel didn't know if they were still being followed, but she would certainly not be able to catch up.
Further on, Nyssi clung desperately, while Thassalin flew around, firing blasts of flames at the dark creature. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight, and the fireballs seemed to have the expected effect. When Thassalin stood up, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw his gun, a reliable rifle. It wasn't of course designed for this kind of situation, but a burst of shots would surely at least deter the black beast, wouldn't they.
